initialize() = put object into initial state, as on construction
setup() = make object ready to use. needs to be called before use.

a& this_a() { return a_; }

define_i()
i_is_defined() --> value to set between contruction and setup

interal_do()  --> virtual function overriden by subbase (Base --> Subbase --> Concrete)


nodes:
- async (async_source)
- sync (sync_source)
- sink
- thin


.h = header (C++)
.cc = module (C++)
.tcc = template implementation (+ some inlines), included at end of .h
.icc = other file included from header (exceptional)

